## Extract swarm-mail as standalone npm package (monorepo conversion)

### Architecture Decision: Adapter Pattern

**Key insight from coursebuilder's adapter-drizzle:** Code against interfaces, accept database as dependency injection.

```typescript
// swarm-mail exports adapter factory
export function createSwarmMailAdapter(db: DatabaseAdapter) {
  return {
    appendEvent: (event) => ...,
    sendMessage: (msg) => ...,
    // etc
  }
}

// Consumer owns database, passes to swarm-mail
const db = new PGlite('./my-db');
const swarmMail = createSwarmMailAdapter(db);
```

### Benefits
- **Portable**: Works with PGLite, Postgres, Turso, any SQL database
- **Testable**: Easy to inject in-memory instances
- **Shareable**: One database instance across multiple consumers
- **Decoupled**: swarm-mail doesn't own database lifecycle

### Interface Design
```typescript
// packages/swarm-mail/src/adapter.ts
export interface DatabaseAdapter {
  query<T>(sql: string, params?: unknown[]): Promise<{ rows: T[] }>;
  exec(sql: string): Promise<void>;
}

export interface SwarmMailAdapter {
  // Event store
  appendEvent(event: AgentEvent): Promise<AgentEvent & { id: number }>;
  readEvents(options?: ReadOptions): Promise<AgentEvent[]>;

  // Agent mail
  sendMessage(msg: MessageInput): Promise<Message>;
  getInbox(agent: string, options?: InboxOptions): Promise<Message[]>;

  // File reservations
  reserveFiles(agent: string, paths: string[]): Promise<Reservation[]>;
  releaseFiles(agent: string): Promise<void>;

  // Locks
  acquireLock(resource: string, holder: string): Promise<Lock>;
  releaseLock(resource: string, holder: string): Promise<void>;
}
```

### Convenience Layer (for simple usage)
```typescript
// packages/swarm-mail/src/pglite.ts
import { PGlite } from '@electric-sql/pglite';
import { createSwarmMailAdapter } from './adapter';

// Singleton cache for convenience API
const instances = new Map<string, SwarmMailAdapter>();

export async function getSwarmMail(projectPath?: string): Promise<SwarmMailAdapter> {
  const dbPath = getDatabasePath(projectPath);
  if (!instances.has(dbPath)) {
    const db = new PGlite(dbPath);
    await runMigrations(db);
    instances.set(dbPath, createSwarmMailAdapter(db));
  }
  return instances.get(dbPath)!;
}
